headline: CDW Inks Deal To Buy Amplified IT; Street Says Buy
summary: CDW Corporation, a multi-brand technology solutions provider, has agreed to snap up Amplified IT, a leading education-focused consultancy for an undisclosed sum. CDW (CDW) expects the deal to be minimally accretive to adjusted EPS for the year 2021. The financial terms and other details of the deal were not disclosed. Virginia-based Amplified IT, a Google Premium education partner, works with its team of Google Cloud professionals to provide insights, services, consulting, and solutions to help schools get the most out of the Google Cloud. CDW CEO Christine A. Leahy said, “The combination of Amplified IT’s focus on educator support and technical skills with CDW’s scale, reach, and leading market position in education will accelerate our collective ability to help schools leverage technology to achieve even greater educational outcomes.” (See CDW stock analysis on TipRanks) Last month, CDW reported 4Q results. The company’s 4Q adjusted earnings climbed 16% year-over-year to reach $1.82 per share and outpaced Street estimates of $1.51. Net sales increased 9.2% to $4.96 billion and exceeded analysts’ expectations of $4.39 billion.
